<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Global Consumer and Small Business Banking (GCSBB) serves more than 59 million consumers and mass-market small business relationships across America through a distribution network of 6,100 banking centers, 18,500 ATMs, and the nation&#39;s leading online bill pay and mobile banking services, as well as through a world class sales forces and call centers.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
This direct hire program is designed to provide external candidates in a variety of masters and PhD programs with an opportunity to prepare for future opportunities in the Consumer and Small Business Banking (CSBB) eChannels and Customer Solutions team. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
The Consumer and Small Business Banking Product Leader Development Program develops future senior leaders while engaging them in challenging projects critical to the future of Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America. Recent Masters-level and PhD graduates experience two to three rotational assignments nine months each over 18-24 months.
</p>
<p class="bac">
Opportunities for direct hire positions include:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Usability Engineer</li>
	<li>Innovation Analyst</li>
	<li>Business Development Analyst</li>
	<li>Business Planning/Strategy Analyst</li>
	<li>eCommerce Product Consultant</li>
	<li>Web Designer</li>
	<li>Visual Design Staff</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
Key Facts about Global Consumer and Small Business Banking Internship:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Each assignment is carefully selected according to the developmental needs of each individual participant</li>
	<li>Each position offers a wide range of responsibilities and business opportunities for the direct hire associate  </li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Ideal candidate will exhibit a strong drive for results; succeed in a fast-paced, empowered, and collaborative environment; enjoy teamwork and partnering with others; possess excellent organizational and analytical skills; understand technology and business requirements.  The ability to learn the organizational structure and the formal/informal workings of the organization and to convey a strong sense of customer and associate satisfaction to drive shareholder value is required.  Additionally requirements include:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>MBA/Master&#39;s or PhD graduate from an accredited business school or University</li>
	<li>Spring/Summer 2010 graduation date</li>
	<li>3–5 years pre-M.B.A./Master&#39;s or PhD work experience with a demonstrated record of achievement </li>
	<li>Relevant work history that reflects experience in supervising others, delegating tasks and resolving conflicts </li>
	<li>Must have eligibility to work in US</li>
	<li>Geographic mobility</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
Preferred expertise and/or experience in at least 3 of the following: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Web Design and visual communications</li>
	<li>Electronic product development/support</li>
	<li>User experience and Usability Engineering </li>
	<li>User experience design</li>
	<li>Innovation Analyst, Business Development Analyst or Business Planning/Strategy within eCommerce</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
Personal characteristics:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Ability to successfully navigate in a complex environment</li>
	<li>Strong leadership potential</li>
	<li>Results oriented, proven high level of performance</li>
	<li>Ability to manage tight deadlines, organize, and prioritize work independently </li>
	<li>Flexibility in exploring a variety of business areas</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

